  "analysis": "We are at /app with no prior commands executed and no existing implementation shown. The task requires creating a single-file React app in /app/index.html using CDN React/ReactDOM/Babel, with a file picker for .md/.markdown/.pdf, automatic analysis on load, and rendering analysis JSON into <pre id="analysis-output">. We need to implement markdown parsing (citations, keyword counts/density, section summaries) and PDF text extraction (likely via pdf.js CDN) with similar analysis and summaries.",
  "plan": "1) Inspect current /app contents to see if index.html exists. 2) Create/overwrite /app/index.html implementing the React UI, analysis logic, and JSON mirror. 3) Use pdf.js via CDN to extract text from PDFs client-side. 4) Add robust parsing helpers: word counting, citation counting with regex, keyword frequencies and densities, section summary extraction for markdown and approximate heading recovery for PDFs. 5) Ensure analysis output is consistent JSON with required fields and updates automatically when a file is loaded.",
  "commands": [
    {
